latestIgtvVideos.caption:
9 years of knowing each other, 7 years of a long distance relationship, 1 year of planning the wedding with covid changing our plans 3 times. This was one hell of a ride. 

Initially, we were supposed to get married in Bhubneswar, my home town. But covid changed our plans. Due to covid norms in Bhubneswar we changed the wedding destination to Hyderabad. And then again as our close relatives got infected with covid we had to change the date.

We had to plan everything all over again. But as they say, the 3rd time is a charm! So we finally got married on 27th January 2022.

The kind of emotions I felt during this wedding can’t be explained. I hardly ever lived without my parents and staying without them is the toughest thing that I have to do. But I am just going to a new house, starting my life with a new wonderful family, and no matter what, I will always be their little daughter who is what she is because of all the effort they, my parents, have put to make me an independent and confident woman ❤️ If it was not for them, I would not be half of what or who I am today. 

#cheerstonewbeginnings

latestIgtvVideos.title: Surprise proposal in my engagement ceremony ♥️💍
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I remember how I always used to tell him how much I love watching proposal videos, just seeing the joy in the faces of those couples and how much I wanted to feel such a moment myself. It's just such a special moment of life that I wanted to experience.

But unfortunately, due to the pandemic, we couldn't meet for a year, which was difficult as it is! Sooo, once our engagement date was fixed, I had it in my mind that it would be a super traditional event and never thought I'd get the kind of proposal I had dreamt of.

I even recall discussing it with him and he had said to me that he was extremely shy to even go down on his knees at our engagement ceremony.

But, to my absolute joy and surprise, along with his whole family, he had this amazing flash mob proposal prepared for me! It was so unexpected because  during the Roka, they had made the both of us sit in front of the dance floor, right in the middle, I assumed it was because that was where the families wanted us to sit during the ceremony. And then out of nowhere, music started playing and his sisters started dancing, at first I thought it was a surprise performance for us by his friends and family. I even kept asking Shray if he knew about it and he kept denying it, and as we were watching, this amazing guy just stands up suddenly and starts dancing too! The sheer astonishment on my face and the joy that started to spread through my heart! Uff! The emotions I felt while he was dancing, and as he looked at me, can never be explained in words!
I was so shocked, overwhelmed and ecstatic, not to forget feeling thousands of eyes on the both of us as they watched all of it.
To be honest, I never thought that day, at the ceremony, it would end with him proposing, but he did! And it felt like an absolute dream.

I guess for a couple of days after that night, I was still in awe of it all. It was honestly the most beautiful surprise of my life. It was a dream come true in so many ways!
I cherish that night forever. I hope to watch this video even after 50 years and feel the same love and happines.

Celebrated 10 years of us at @kokohyderabad , and honestly, couldn’t have picked a better spot.
From the moment we walked in, everything felt just right — the ambiance, the vibe, and oh my god… the food.

I’m not someone who usually blogs about restaurants or does food reviews (so you know I really mean it when I say this) — every single dish we tried was outstanding. The kind of meal where you don’t want to share a bite but you still do because it’s that good.
The tom yum noodles? Unreal. The sushi? So fresh. The spicy cocktail? Had a kick and a half. And that pecan butter dessert? Let’s just say I’m still dreaming about it.

It wasn’t just a dinner, it was an experience — and the perfect way to celebrate a decade of love, laughter, and everything in between.
KOKO, you have my heart (and a returning customer).
.
.
.

An ASMR road trip through the soul of Wayanad 🌿✨
At the end of March, we set off on a peaceful road trip from Bangalore to Wayanad with mom and dad—what followed was a slow, soul-stirring escape into the heart of nature.

As we drove through the dense forests of Nagarhole, we were greeted by the wild—deer and elephants crossing the roads, birds soaring overhead, and the soothing hush of the trees swaying in rhythm. Nature felt alive, and so did we.

We stayed at the serene @tajwayanadkerala perched amidst the hills with a view that looked straight out of a painting. The mornings were misty, the air crisp, and the silence felt like a warm embrace.

Our journey took a beautiful turn when we met our adventure hosts from @hipnoeticstays , who helped us discover Wayanad beyond the usual. They took us to a humble village cottage by a pond, where an elderly couple welcomed us with the warmest smiles. We tried fishing, enjoyed a quiet boat ride, picked fresh fruits, and savoured the most comforting home-cooked meal prepared with love and simplicity.

But the highlight? A hidden waterfall tucked away inside a secluded tea estate. 🌱
Surrounded by emerald green leaves, wildflowers, and tall trees—this untouched slice of paradise was just ours to explore. A single ray of sunlight made its way through the canopy and lit up the waterfall like a spotlight. The only sounds were gushing water, birdsong, and the wind—it felt sacred.

This wasn’t just a trip—it was a reminder to slow down, breathe deeper, and listen.
Listen to the land. To the stillness. To yourself.

🎧 Put on your earphones and experience Wayanad like we did—through every whisper, ripple, and rustle.
